5 I've been coming to this Fausto's for a few years now and it has been my number one choice to satisfy my Mexican food cravings. It's a quaint little joint much like the other Mexican grills and eateries around town. The service is quick and friendly and the food is always yum. Their portions are SOMETIMES inconsistent but that's never been a deal breaker for me. Breakfast, lunch or dinner, Fausto's never disappoints.   If you're not too sure of what to get, my top choices consist of the following:  Carnitas Plate  California Burrito (Stuffed Fries)  Breakfast Burritos  Fish Tacos  And of course, the Carne Asada Fries!  Also, be sure to take full advantage of their salsa bar! Limes, pickled jalapeños/carrots, and 3 types of sauces to perfectly pair with your meal. Happy Eats!
